{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id4cda001c-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10705"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"10705"},"text":"§ 10705.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this subchapter:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4cda001d-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10705/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “first responder” includes a firefighter, law enforcement officer, paramedic, emergency medical technician, or other individual (including an employee of a legally organized and recognized volunteer organization, whether compensated or not), who, in the course of his or her professional duties, responds to fire, medical, hazardous material, or other similar emergencies.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4cda001e-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10705/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “medication-assisted treatment” means the use of medications approved by the Food and Drug Administration for the treatment of opioid abuse.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4cda001f-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10705/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “opioid” means any drug, including heroin, having an addiction-forming or addiction-sustaining liability similar to morphine or being capable of conversion into a drug having such addiction-forming or addiction-sustaining liability.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4cda0020-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10705/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “schedule II, III, or IV controlled substance” means a controlled substance that is listed on schedule II, schedule III, or schedule IV of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s812/c"},"text":"section 812(c) of title 21","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4cda0021-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10705/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The terms “drug” and “device” have the meanings given those terms in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s321"},"text":"section 321 of title 21","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4cda0022-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10705/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “criminal justice agency” means a State, local, or tribal—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4cda0023-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10705/6/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" court;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4cda0024-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10705/6/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" prison;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4cda0025-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10705/6/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" jail;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4cda0026-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10705/6/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" law enforcement agency; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4cda0027-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10705/6/E"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"E"},"text":"(E)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" other agency that performs the administration of criminal justice, including prosecution, pretrial services, and community supervision.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4cda0028-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10705/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “tribal organization” has the meaning given that term in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s5304"},"text":"section 5304 of title 25","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4cda0029-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s10705/8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8"},"text":"(8)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “State substance abuse agency” has the meaning given that term in section 290bb–1(r)(6) ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002060"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag"